of medically used 110mIn

x4freetext: Activation method was used. Irradiation were
done at 65 and 70 MeV proton energies.
The beam was extracted from the cyclotron and
the irradiation was done in a Faraday-type target
holder.
Stacked target irradiation technique was
applied.
Energy degradation in each layers the stack
was calculated by using the semi-empirical polynomial
formula of Ziegler and Andersen.
Nondestructive gamma-spectrometry was used.
The beam energy and intensity were monitored
Chapter 4
includes the uncertainty of the primary beam
energy and straggling effect.

Fitted excitation functions were used for
